Gambia, with a population of just over 2 million, has reported 2743 cases since the outbreak in March, and 93 deaths. The daily reported cases we Cases have increased exponentially in the country, which is mostly surrounded by Senegal, in the last couple of weeks, prompting the government to re-impose restrictive measures. Neighbouring Senegal has reported 13 294 cases with 277 deaths. Public gatherings in Gambia have been banned, dusk-to-dawn curfew declared, and schools remain closed. Places of worship may remain open with restrictive safety measures in place, the statement said. --Reuters--